      • getActualConstValue

        default java.lang.Object getActualConstValue()
        If all invocations of the method pass the same value to the parameter, returns that value (the name of a static final field or the text of a literal expression). Otherwise, returns VALUE_IS_NOT_CONST.
        Returns:
        the parameter value or null if it's different or impossible to determine.
